fields.subtitle: Travel Lodging Marketplace
fields.description: YourCribs provides users an opportunity to find, book and host private and unique sleeping accommodations ("cribs") across the United States. Users book locations from private hosts, and can message hosts and review "cribs" after their visit.
fields.impact: One-week coding sprint on a small team of two developers at Coding Dojo. I developed the back- and front-end features for users to host and book places, including logic to block users from booking a location on dates that already have a scheduled booking.

fields.subtitle: Personal Portfolio
fields.description: Yes, the page you are currently viewing. I built this page from scratch, using some inspiration from other portfolio examples. But it is not simply a single-page application. I used Python's Django framework to build a back end application to help me manage the page features.
fields.impact: Each of the sections of the page you are viewing are separate components or text files. The back end application provides features to manage skills, projects, images, site traffic, and messaging services. The page makes heavy use of JavaScript and AJAX.

fields.subtitle: Chat Messaging
fields.description: DojoSlack provides asynchronous chat messaging for collaborative teams. Teams may organize and search conversations on separate channels.
fields.impact: One-week coding sprint on a small team of three developers at Coding Dojo. I developed the back- and front-end features for asynchronous messaging services with heavy use of Angular's observables.

fields.subtitle: User Reviews and Recommendations
fields.description: The world needs more yodelers. Yodel provides users a platform to shout out reviews for local restaurants, bars, service providers, and other places of business.
fields.impact: One-week coding sprint on a small team of two developers at Coding Dojo. I developed the back- and front-end features for users to create pages for businesses, search for businesses, generate a review on a business.

fields.subtitle: Nonprofit Case Management Application
fields.description: Case Management tracks critical case information for refugee families that recently arrived in the United States and are adjusting to their new surroundings. The database maintains personal information, case notes, financial expenses, health information, and progress toward defined objectives. I significantly expanded the database features and functions to aggregate data, auto-generate management reports, correlate case data with other important metrics, and simplify the user interface for ease-of-use. The new features significantly reduced the amount of time required to complete compliance audits and increased staff capacity to handle a 33% surge in operations.
fields.impact:
While this was an outdated Microsoft Access database project, the work I did on this had a profound impact on World Relief's operations, and provided the motivation to pursue web-based database development. 
Timeframe: 2014-2016

fields.subtitle: Nonprofit Volunteer Management
fields.description:
Volunteer manager provides an integrated volunteer and donor relationship manager (similar to a CRM platform) for World Relief, a Chicago-based nonprofit refugee resettlement agency. When I started working at World Relief, I noticed that the volunteer managers lost a lot of time and energy attempting to keep track of an extensive network of volunteers through numerous complicated spreadsheets. I offered to create a new database system that would help them track volunteers more efficiently. Volunteer Manager tracks volunteers through an application system, events volunteers attend, organizations or churches the volunteers are related to, and connects volunteers to the Refugee Case Management application. The database also tracks donor information and generates aggregate reports for management.

The deployed database saved World Relief many hours of work effort every month, and substantially increased staff capacity to know volunteers and assign them to work tasks more effectively.
fields.impact:
While this was an outdated Microsoft Access database project, the work I did on this had a profound impact on World Relief's operations, and provided the motivation to pursue web-based database development. 
Timeframe: 2016
